entries.femaleVariant: The whole clan knows we set out tomorrow.
They know why, what our aim is?
So you wanna tunnel into Arasaka Tower.
I know how it sounds. But we'd be plumb fools not to take advantage.
You see, Night Corp's building a new maglev line in the area. Granted, it's guarded by Militech, but they're nothing we can't handle.
Once we're in that tunnel, it's just half a mile to the substratum levels of Arasaka Tower.
They're using one of Night Corp's SERCs. It would only need a few minutes to dig that distance.
How you expect to handle Militech at the construction site?
Come find us later. I'll leave you in Saul's hands now.
Construction site – whadda we got for security? Whole place spiked? Militech out in full force?
It's your average hard-hat area – nothing too scary. But we can't just walk past 'em.
I'll talk to our brothers and sisters, get a drone buzzing over that site.
Needed some sleep, is all. Heard you were already cookin' up a plan?
We still have details to iron out, but we know the who, where and how.
Wanna dig under 'Saka Tower.
And we know this'll work?
Sure these plans're up-to-date, completely reliable?
Positively. We went to our Snake Nation sources.
They've been turning stones over in that area.
I'm not one to lie, this tunnel gambit is risky. But if it works, that's our way into Mikoshi.
We'll need bucketloads more information. It's the only way to determine if this plan holds water.
It'll prove full of holes no matter what we turn up, Saul, I can tell you that already.
Ahh. Panam is right. We have to accept these risks come what may. That much we owe you.
So, V, I heard talk that there's a war comin'.
[Lean on table] I'm fine. Let's go over the plan.
Have a look for yourself.
A few strategies we sussed out.
But only one grants us a decent shot at penetrating Arasaka Tower.
We'll dig a tunnel.
A Subterranean Extraction and Removal Combine. It's... automated tunnel boring.
If we can grab one, we'll dig through to Arasaka Tower, then go on to Mikoshi.
'Fraid I don't got a choice, Mitch.
Looks like we don't have one, neither.
Come on, I'll take you to see them.
Look around, V. War-tested veterans are a fistful at most. The rest mostly raid rinky-dink convoys and salvage scrap.
So for now they know only as much as they need to know – the aim is to help you out.
The plan is solid, Saul. Do not go muddying the waters. Not now.
Fuck, you think I don't know that?
We're sending this clan to its grave.
And yet you seem to think you can change something by chewing me out like you usually do!
V! Finally.
How's your health?
But what's the alternative? To call off the assault? To let her die?
entries.maleVariant: But what's the alternative? To call off the assault? To let him die?

entries.femaleVariant: We expect to see the usual – drone patrols, on-site operators, restricted access.
The plan, entire op – it's about headin' into enemy territory. You'll make enemies of Arasaka and others.
So it appears.
I'm exposin' you – all of you – to danger. Want out, wanna cut your losses, I'd understand, no hard feelings.
You came to us for help, we decided we'd provide it. Our minds are made up – no more discussion needed.
It's settled. We had best get to work.
And I'll check with Mitch – I think I know how to even the odds against Militech.
Is there anything else you need?
Just, no making decisions without me.
Need to get in touch with Alt.
You and Panam agreeing all right?
Hey, you and Panam – something I need to know about?
Need a decent net-connection. Someone I know can help us get into Mikoshi.
Alt. An AI. I need her help.
Who might that be?
Long story.
Long story.
V, allow me to be blunt. I don't like that the particulars of this raid could venture outside this tent or this family.
But do what you must.
Alt. She-- It's... an AI from... out past the Blackwall.
entries.maleVariant: Alt. She's-- It's... an AI from... out past the Blackwall.

entries.femaleVariant: Are you fully present up there? Why in hell would an AI help us break into Mikoshi?
'Cause I'll ask it to, nicely.
Fuck me, V…
Find Dakota. She'll get you geared up, no questions asked.
Thanks, Saul.
Thank me once we get out of Mikoshi alive and in one piece.
Doesn't ring true to me, that.
Panam think so, too?
Doubt that's entirely true.
Panam think so too?
I don't have any hard feelings towards you, V. The opposite, in fact.
You'd have to ask her yourself.
See, V, you're like the outsider who happens upon a family and witnesses nothing but endless quarrels.
Then all of a sudden the outsider's presence is noticed, and the family members shake hands, join hands, become stronger than they were before.
Understand?
Yeah. 'Least, I think so.
Good. So now you can tell me what else you'll need.
Not bad, wouldn't you say?
What's a SERC?
Sounds doable in theory to me. No competin' ideas, then let's get to preppin'.
entries.maleVariant: Sounds doable in theory to me. No competing ideas, then let's get to prepping.

entries.femaleVariant: SERC – what's that?
It'll have to do... for lack of a better plan.
You can still change your minds.
[Lean on table] Been better. Whatcha got for me?
Been better.
So, what've you guys patched together?
Mhm.
Think so.
What happened?
Got no choice in the matter.
And so she lives.
Well, if it ain't V! How's that head of yours, sister?
entries.maleVariant: Well, if it ain't V! How's that head of  yours, brother?

entries.femaleVariant: Hey, Teddy.
Welcome back to the living. Ya feelin' OK?
Um, I guess...?
Mighty good to hear.
What happened?
You passed out on the way.
V, any thoughts?
I thought we'd smoothed over the rough edges between us. Then you showed up.
It's funny you should ask.
Once we're in, we'll have to improvise. Guards, security measures, the fastest way into Mikoshi – we'll take things as they come and hope for the best.
One you assume I'd rather not hear, hm?
You know what? Fine. We're up to our balls in dung anyway. Might as well go deeper.
You had us worried back there. You passed out, and we couldn't shake you awake.
Panam asked me to keep an eagle eye on you.
Where'd she go?
She's off debating Saul. You need help – that's clear. They sat right down to figure out how we might do that.
We tried shaking you awake –  to no avail. It sure does seem like your condition might be getting worse, V.
It sure does seem like your condition might be getting worse.
[Get out]
[Rise] Thank you, Saul.
V? Can you share your thoughts?
